MATCH_TOOL: Edit|Write
MATCH_PATTERN: (isNudgeAllowed|isWhisperAllowed|Social\.NUDGE|Social\.WHISPER|processNudge|processWhisper|trackNudge|channelHasCapability)
ADVISORY: |
  Capability model has one deliberate asymmetry: NUDGE is player-scoped, not
  channel-scoped. `Events.Social.NUDGE` carries only `{ senderId, targetId }` —
  NO channelId. Do NOT add a `channelHasCapability(channelId, 'NUDGE')` check
  to `isNudgeAllowed` — the check can't fire (the field isn't on the event)
  and nudges are intentionally initiated from many contexts (chat chip, DM
  chip, Cast Strip avatar tap, avatar popover in legacy shells).

  The `NUDGE` capability on a channel IS a UI affordance flag — client
  HintChips uses it to decide whether to show the `/nudge` chip for that
  channel. Stripping the cap on 1:1→GROUP_DM promotion hides the chip in
  groups but doesn't (and shouldn't) block NUDGE events at the server.

  WHISPER is different — it IS channel-scoped (always MAIN). `isWhisperAllowed`
  SHOULD check `channelHasCapability(context.channels, 'MAIN', 'WHISPER')`.
  The check needs no channelId on the event because whispers always target
  MAIN.

  Rule of thumb: if an Events.Social.* event type carries `channelId`, the
  guard can cap-check; otherwise cap is a UI affordance flag only.

  Source: docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-13-pulse-dm-polish-design.md
  (§Architecture — "NUDGE is player-scoped, not channel-scoped").
